			'To calculate child support in Texas, start with gross monthly income, estimate Texas child support net resources, then apply the guideline percentage for the number of children before the court. This child support calculator Texas page provides a planning estimate, not an official court calculation.',
		answerHtml:
			'To calculate child support in Texas, start with gross monthly income, estimate Texas child support net resources, then apply the guideline percentage for the number of children before the court. This child support calculator Texas page provides a planning estimate, not an official court calculation. You can also compare parenting time with our <a href="/custody-schedule-generator/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">Texas custody schedule generator</a>.',
